This file exists only so git tracks the (currently empty) public/
directory — the Dockerfile's runner stage does `COPY .../public ./public`,
which fails if the directory doesn't exist at all. Git doesn't track empty
directories, so without this placeholder, deleting the last real file in
public/ silently removes the directory from the repo. If you add real
files here later (a favicon, an image), you can delete this file.
